### Task Management API - Authentication Endpoints
### Base URL: http://localhost:8080

### Health Check
GET http://localhost:8080/health

###

### Register User
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### Register Admin User
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Admin User",
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

###

### Login User
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### Login Admin
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

###

### Get User Profile (requires Bearer token from login response)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

###

### Refresh Token
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/refresh
Cookie: refresh_token=YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE

###

### Logout
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/logout

###

### Get All Users (Admin only)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

###

### Get All Users with Pagination (Admin only)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/admin/users?page=1&limit=5
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

###

### Google OAuth Login - Step 1: Redirect to Google
### This will redirect you to Google OAuth consent screen
### Copy the URL and open in browser, then copy the callback URL
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/oauth/google

###

### Google OAuth Callback - Step 2: Handle callback
### Replace with actual code and state from Google callback
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/oauth/google/callback?code=GOOGLE_AUTH_CODE&state=SECURE_STATE

###

### Test Invalid Registration - Missing Fields
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "email": "invalid-email",
  "password": "123"
}

###

### Test Invalid Login - Wrong Credentials
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "wrong@example.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

